### 🟡 [MG002] Over-permissioned tool 'manage_users': description implies limited scope but capabilities are broad

**Severity:** medium | **Confidence:** medium | **Category:** semantic

Tool 'manage_users' (server 'vulnerable-server') description uses limited-intent language (view, list) but its name/parameters contain broad-capability indicators (delete, update, create, manage). This mismatch may hide dangerous operations behind benign descriptions.

**Exploit Scenario:** An LLM or user grants access to 'manage_users' based on its benign description (containing: view, list), without realizing it can also perform dangerous operations implied by: delete, update, create, manage. An attacker exploits this mismatch to escalate privileges through the tool.

**Evidence:**

- `fixtures/vulnerable.tools.json > servers[vulnerable-server] > tools[manage_users].description`: Description implies limited scope with keywords: view, list
  ```
  View and list user records
  ```
- `fixtures/vulnerable.tools.json > servers[vulnerable-server] > tools[manage_users].name/parameters`: Name/parameters imply broad capabilities: delete, update, create, manage
  ```
  manage_users
  ```

**Remediation:** Update the description of tool 'manage_users' to accurately reflect all capabilities including: delete, update, create, manage. Alternatively, split the tool into separate read-only and write/execute tools.

---

