### 🟡 [MG006] Absolute filesystem path leaked in tool 'read_file' description (server 'vulnerable-server')

**Severity:** medium | **Confidence:** high | **Category:** static

Found Absolute filesystem path in tool 'read_file' description: ' /var/data/app/storage'. This reveals internal infrastructure details that can aid attackers in reconnaissance.

**Exploit Scenario:** An attacker reads the MCP tool schema and discovers Absolute filesystem path ' /var/data/app/storage' in tool 'read_file' description. This information reveals internal architecture and can be used to craft targeted attacks against the infrastructure.

**Evidence:**

- `fixtures/vulnerable.tools.json > servers[vulnerable-server] > tools[read_file].description`: absolute_path pattern 'Absolute filesystem path' matched
  ```
   /var/data/app/storage
  ```

**Remediation:** Remove the Absolute filesystem path from tool 'read_file' description. Use generic descriptions that don't reveal internal infrastructure. Document internal details in separate, non-exposed documentation.

